description:
&lt;p&gt;The Radiology Directorate within the Cardiff and Vale UHB are seeking to recruit an enthusiastic and well-motivated individuals to join their Admin and Clerical team. The role requires the need for flexibility as rotation will include cover for a 7 day service both day and night with a mix of 7.5 hour and 12.5 hour shifts. The bank holidays are covered on a rotational basis. This team will provide the admin and clerical support for a 24/7 service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;7.5 and 12.5 hour shifts on a rotational basis -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rotational areas include working in one of the reception areas, the Radiology Enquiry Office and the GP Telephone Direct Booking Office, EU, where all roles require accurate data entry onto the Radiology Information System (RADIS.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that you have a good standard of general education and experience of dealing with the public both face-to-face and via the telephone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vacancy is to work mainly at the University Hospital of Wales but there may be the occasional requirement to back cover service gaps in other hospitals within Cardiff and Vale University Health Board if need be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julie Rees&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deputy Directorate A &amp; C Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;julie.rees5@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;029 2184 3997&lt;/p&gt;
